modules.description: This module implements flexible arrays using Braun trees, supporting efficient logarithmic-time operations for adding/removing elements at both ends (`cons`, `tail`, `snoc`, `liat`), indexed access and updates (`get`, `set`), and array construction (`make`, `init`, `of_array`, `of_list`). It provides iteration (`iter`, `iteri`), folding (`fold`, `foldi`), and mapping (`map`, `mapi`) functions with linear time complexity, along with pretty-printing (`pp`). Concrete use cases include implementing queues or deques with efficient end operations, managing dynamic collections with indexed access, and transforming arrays with element-wise functions.
